com.maxwellwheeler.plugins.tppets.commands

Class CommandPermissions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.maxwellwheeler.plugins.tppets.commands.CommandPermissions

  • class CommandPermissions
extends java.lang.Object
    Object that processes tpp pet permission commands: /tpp allow [username] [pet name] /tpp remove [username] [pet name] /tpp list [pet name]
    Author:
    GatheringExp

    • Method Detail

      • allowPlayer

        public void allowPlayer(org.bukkit.command.CommandSender sender,
                        java.lang.String[] args)
        Syntax: /tpp allow [username] [pet name] Allows the player with [username] to your pet with [pet name] Alternative Syntax: /tpp allow from:[username 1] [username 2] [pet name] Allows [username 2] to [username 1]'s pet named [pet name]
        Parameters:
        sender - The CommandSender object that originally sent the command.
        args - The arguments passed with the command - doesn't include the "tpp allow" in command. Ex: /tpp allow GatheringExp MyPet, String args[] would have {GatheringExp, MyPet}.

      • addAllowedPlayer

        private CommandPermissions.EditResult addAllowedPlayer(org.bukkit.OfflinePlayer from,
                                                       java.lang.String addedPlayerName,
                                                       java.lang.String petName)
        Generic processor for /tpp allow [args] commands
        Parameters:
        from - The player the command is to be processed from. Because Player extends OfflinePlayer, this can be the player that ran the command, or a player running the command for someone else
        addedPlayerName - The name to add to the above "from" object's pet.
        petName - The pet name to add addedPlayerName to.
        Returns:
        Enum representing the success/failure of the command

      • listPlayers

        public void listPlayers(org.bukkit.command.CommandSender sender,
                        java.lang.String[] args)
        Syntax: /tpp list [pet name] Lists all players allowed to sender's [pet name] Alternative Syntax: /tpp list from:[username] [pet name] Lists all players allowed to [username]'s [pet name]
